This paper deals with the problem of learning regression functions from pairwise data, which is a common problem in machine learning. The focus of the paper is on enforcing prior knowledge of symmetry or anti-symmetry in the relation to be learned, which is a common technique in kernel methods. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves spectral analysis, which is a common technique in signal processing and graph theory, making cs.SI (Signal and Image Processing) a likely sub-category as well. Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of approximation properties and regularization bias, which are common topics in theoretical computer science, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible sub-category.
